criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  individuals of both sexes;

          -  without communication, vision, hearing or intellectual disabilities;

          -  capable of mental to fill in the questionnaires;

          -  who watch at least 5 minutes of the video, minimum physiological immersion time.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  use of sedatives;

          -  those who experience considerable discomfort possibly caused by virtual reality such
             as nausea, dizziness or headache, with a history of vertigo, nausea, vomiting;

          -  convulsion, labyrinthitis, epilepsy, dementia, mental confusion, psychomotor
             agitation;

          -  claustrophobia or expressing a desire to discontinue the study;

          -  patients who use anticholinergic drugs (antipsychotics and benzodiazepines);

          -  delirium;

          -  clinical worsening.
